section.def:
acceptance
                (承兌) means an acceptance completed by delivery or
            notification;

action
                (法律行動) means action or suit and includes
            counterclaim and set-off;

banker
                (銀行) includes a body of persons, whether
            incorporated or not, who carry on the business of banking;

bearer
                (持票人) means the person in possession of a bill or
            note which is payable to bearer;

delivery
                (交付) means transfer of possession, actual or
            constructive, from one person to another;

holder
                (持有人) means the payee or indorsee of a bill or
            note who is in possession of it, or the bearer thereof;

indorsement
                (背書) means an indorsement completed by
            delivery;

issue
                (發給) means the first delivery of a bill or note,
            complete in form, to a person who takes it as a holder;

person
                (人) includes a body of persons, whether
            incorporated or not;

subparagraph.content:
interest thereon from the time of presentment for payment, if the bill is
                    payable on demand, and from the maturity of the bill in any other
                    case;

paragraph.content:
where a bill payable to, or to the order of, a third party is paid by the
                    drawer, the drawer may enforce payment thereof against the acceptor, but may not
                    reissue the bill;

subparagraph.content:
where a bill is issued out of Hong Kong, it is not invalid by reason
                        only that it is not stamped in accordance with the law of the place of
                        issue;

paragraph.content:
in determining what is a reasonable time, regard shall be had to the nature of
                the instrument, the usage of trade and of bankers, and the facts of the particular
                case;

the words “and company”, or any abbreviation thereof, between two parallel
                    transverse lines, either with or without the words “not negotiable”;
                    or

acceptance
                        suprà
                    protest;
